                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d706">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102S/1192: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai (<persName
                            corresp="frus1932v03#p_CES1" type="from">Cunningham</persName>) to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-06-04T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >June 4, 1932—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 4—2:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>280. A representative of Greater Shanghai and the Shanghai Municipal Council
                    initialed a <hi rend="italic">modus vivendi</hi> this morning covering
                    extra-Settlement roads and other questions. The agreement will not be published
                    until it has been offered to Municipal Council and the Chinese Government for
                    approval. I shall comment on the agreement in the next few days.</p>
                <p>Repeated to the Legation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_CES1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cunningham</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
